  "original_title": "\u0daf\u0dda\u0dc1\u0db4\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0db1\u0da5\u0dba\u0db1\u0dca \u0d85\u0dc3\u0dd6\u0dc0\u0d9a\u0da7 \u0d85\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dc3\u0dca \u0daf\u0dd6\u0dc2\u0dab \u0da0\u0ddd\u0daf\u0db1\u0dcf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Eighty politicians accused of bribery and corruption",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Bribery or Corruption Allegations Investigation Commission says that 386 people, including 80 politicians of various ranks including ministers, have been investigated for bribery and corruption.",
        "In addition to this, a senior official of the commission told Lankadeepa on Sunday that investigations are being conducted against forty-two people, including a former minister, regarding the allegations of illegal acquisition of assets.",
        "These investigations have been started between January 1st and June 30th of this year.",
        "Meanwhile, the officer also mentioned that 22 bribery-related raids have been conducted during that period.",
        "Officials of the Commission point out that the Commission of Investigation of Bribery and Corruption Allegations of Bribery and Corruption and Illegal Gaining of Assets has made a number of prosecutions this year.",
        "Meanwhile, due to the economic inflationary situation, it is said from the sources of the commission that there has been some increase in the cases of bribery all over the island."
      ],
